<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/webpro/wordpress/highlights-wordcamp-toronto-2016/">Highlights from WordCamp Toronto 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage">Garage</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:91:"https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wordcamp-toronto-2016-305x170.jpg";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Andy McIlwain";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9001:"<p>WordCamp Toronto holds a special place in my heart. I helped organize the event from 2011 through 2015, and did the same with the <a href="https://meetup.com/wptoronto" target="_blank">local WordPress meetup group</a>¬†during that time. So for the last six years, it‚Äôs played a big role in my life, and it‚Äôs been a core part of how I introduce myself to others.</p>
<p>Many ‚Äî if not most ‚Äî of my professional relationships have come from this community. So when I show up at a local event like WordCamp Toronto 2016, it feels like a reunion. For a good chunk of attendees, we‚Äôre beyond being contacts or colleagues or connections; we‚Äôre friends. And that adds a whole other dimension to the WordCamp experience.</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">Getting <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> weekend underway with <a href="https://twitter.com/andymci">@andymci</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/mhanes">@mhanes</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/brentkobayashi">@brentkobayashi</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/pbearne">@pbearne</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/brianrotsztein">@brianrotsztein</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/wpmodder">@wpmodder</a> <a href="https://t.co/7HPPjykOmp">pic.twitter.com/7HPPjykOmp</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Shawn Hooper (@ShawnHooper) <a href="https://twitter.com/ShawnHooper/status/761688170651975680">August 5, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>As a Torontonian, I was happy to see WordCamp Toronto 2016 move into the downtown core. There‚Äôs a lot to love about our city, but out-of-town visitors haven‚Äôt experienced much of it during the last few WordCamps.</p>
<p>This time, attendees were steps from all of the major tourist attractions, and most everything else was a quick transit ride or cab ride away.</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">While you&#39;re here&#8230; don&#39;t forget to get a photo in front of the Toronto sign! <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/protips?src=hash">#protips</a> <a href="https://t.co/PT5QnhDlzs">pic.twitter.com/PT5QnhDlzs</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Andy McIlwain (@andymci) <a href="https://twitter.com/andymci/status/761647211344171008">August 5, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>I was happy that the event moved into August. It‚Äôs the best possible weather you‚Äôll get in Toronto. A number of attendees even planned mini-vacations around #WCTO16 this year so they could squeeze in some recreation and relaxation time. (You don‚Äôt see much of that in the middle of November!)</p>
<p>And I was also happy to see so many new speakers coming to Toronto, some coming all the way from eastern Europe, or from the southwestern United States. (We often have folks coming up from the midwest, upstate New York, and New England, but they‚Äôre practically family at this point.)<br />
Overheard at WordCamp Toronto 2016<br />
So, with Toronto pride out of the way ‚Ä¶ here‚Äôs a bit of what we overheard this year.</p>
<h4><a href="https://twitter.com/shawnhooper" target="_blank">Shawn Hooper</a>¬†got some well-deserved praise from our friends at <a href="https://twitter.com/SiteLock/" target="_blank">SiteLock</a>.</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr"><a href="https://twitter.com/ShawnHooper">@ShawnHooper</a> wins the award for ‚Äúbest advice‚Äù slide at <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> session! <a href="https://t.co/agDYp6PMjt">pic.twitter.com/agDYp6PMjt</a></p>
<p>&mdash; SiteLock (@SiteLock) <a href="https://twitter.com/SiteLock/status/762306366140780544">August 7, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="https://twitter.com/TomAuger" target="_blank">Tom Auger</a>¬†shared insights about user empathy and crafting brilliant UX.</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">Thanks for attending my talk at <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> on <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/UX?src=hash">#UX</a>. Here are the slides on GitHub &#8211; do with them as you wish! <a href="https://t.co/QjbI4e3b2h">https://t.co/QjbI4e3b2h</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Tom Auger (@TomAuger) <a href="https://twitter.com/TomAuger/status/762339453939675144">August 7, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="https://twitter.com/michelleames" target="_blank">Michelle Ames</a>¬†showed off the surprise speaker gift: pannier messenger bags!</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">Awesome speaker swag! <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> <a href="https://t.co/bV0654UKPZ">pic.twitter.com/bV0654UKPZ</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Michelle Ames (@michelleames) <a href="https://twitter.com/michelleames/status/762001524730040320">August 6, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>Meanwhile, <a href="https://twitter.com/tapps" target="_blank">Tracy Apps</a>¬†reminded everyone that designers aren‚Äôt ‚Äúpixel pushers.‚Äù</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">thanks to everyone who attended designers != pixel pushers! if you missed the link, my slides are at <a href="https://t.co/LrMtBxiUFF">https://t.co/LrMtBxiUFF</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/wcto?src=hash">#wcto</a></p>
<p>&mdash; tracy apps (@tapps) <a href="https://twitter.com/tapps/status/761989131249520640">August 6, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><a href="https://twitter.com/thebillygregory" target="_blank">Billy Gregory</a>¬†touched on user experience, too ‚Äî specifically what we can do to make the web more accessible for all.</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">Web accessibility is always changing. &quot;We need to evolve.&quot; <a href="https://twitter.com/thebillygregory">@thebillygregory</a> at <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/WCTO16?src=hash">#WCTO16</a> cameo <a href="https://twitter.com/jared_w_smith">@jared_w_smith</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/a11y?src=hash">#a11y</a> <a href="https://t.co/5nhlCf097Y">pic.twitter.com/5nhlCf097Y</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Anthony D Paul (@anthonydpaul) <a href="https://twitter.com/anthonydpaul/status/761928139245223937">August 6, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>There were even ukulele jam sessions!</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="entry-content-asset">
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550">
<p lang="en" dir="ltr">My favourite <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/wcto16?src=hash">#wcto16</a> moment <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f496.png" alt="üíñ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f496.png" alt="üíñ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/72x72/1f496.png" alt="üíñ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/ukelele?src=hash">#ukelele</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/wcukelele?src=hash">#wcukelele</a> <a href="https://t.co/92BNuiA692">https://t.co/92BNuiA692</a> <a href="https://t.co/RTS0cNBpr6">pic.twitter.com/RTS0cNBpr6</a></p>
<p>&mdash; Meagan (@mhanes) <a href="https://twitter.com/mhanes/status/762351677886328832">August 7, 2016</a></p></blockquote>
<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
<p>Many thanks to the organizers, volunteers, and speakers for making WordCamp Toronto 2016 happen.</p>
<p>And if you‚Äôre reading this and <em>didn‚Äôt</em> make it to Toronto this year: see you in 2017! Drop me a line and we‚Äôll grab a Timmies.</p>
