<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/webpro/wordpress/adding-enticing-restaurant-menus-wordpress-website/">Adding enticing restaurant menus to your WordPress website</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage">Garage</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:85:"https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WordPress-menus-305x170.jpg";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:10:"image/jpeg";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Tom Ewer";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11212:"<p>Though the bad old days of impossible-to-navigate, Flash-based fiascos are largely behind us, restaurant websites remain difficult to get <em>completely</em> right. One of the main areas where many restaurant sites drop the ball is in their presentation of restaurant menus.</p>
<blockquote><p>Outside of presenting crystal clear details of location and opening hours, making a menu that‚Äôs easy to find and read may be the most crucial job a restaurant website has. Despite this seemingly obvious requirement, it‚Äôs astonishing how many sites still make reading restaurant menus a chore for users.</p></blockquote>
<p>Fortunately, WordPress has a number of easy-to-implement solutions available to help tackle this task. In this piece, we‚Äôll highlight four options ‚Äì two themes and two plugins ‚Äì but before we get down to business, let‚Äôs briefly remind ourselves why it‚Äôs so important to get restaurant menus right.</p>
<h2>Why your restaurant site needs an enticing menu</h2>
<p>There‚Äôs a reason virtually every restaurant on earth makes its menu easily readable outside their establishment. People want to know what they serve ‚Äì and how much it‚Äôs going to cost ‚Äì before they go through the door.</p>
<p>This is as true online as it is offline ‚Äì a 2015 study by the <a href="http://www.restaurant.org/" target="_blank">National Restaurant Association</a>¬†showed that 70 percent of <a href="http://www.singleplatform.com/blog/2015/02/11/15-key-stats-nras-restaurant-industry-forecast/" target="_blank">smartphone users</a>¬†view restaurant menus on their phones at least a few times per year. Against that type of background, going for solutions not optimized for all browsing situations (such as offering PDF menus) simply isn‚Äôt going to cut the mustard.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre tackling a restaurant website project today, you basically have two choices in terms of implementing a slick menu solution in WordPress: go with a dedicated restaurant theme, or integrate a standalone restaurant menu plugin.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs look at some choices for both options.</p>
<h2>WordPress restaurant themes with solid menu options</h2>
<p>A number of solid themes aimed directly at the restaurant market have emerged over the last few years. Pick the right one to base your project on, and you can kill several birds with one stone: optimal display on smart devices, slick visual presentation, booking integration options, and an intuitive way of easily displaying menus should all come as standard.</p>
<p>You‚Äôll find <a href="http://www.codeinwp.com/blog/restaurant-wordpress-themes/" target="_blank">restaurant theme roundups</a>¬†aplenty online, but the following two selections stand out from the crowd, and more than deliver on the menu front.</p>
<h4>Canap√© from Automattic</h4>
<p>Using an <a href="https://automattic.com/" target="_blank">Automattic</a>¬†theme is generally a guarantee of high standards and carefully considered details throughout. As <a href="https://wptavern.com/canape-an-elegant-free-restaurant-theme-for-wordpress" target="_blank">WP Tavern‚Äôs review</a>¬†makes clear, the recently launched <a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/canape/" target="_blank">Canap√©</a>¬†is no exception to this rule.</p>
<div id="attachment_15799" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Canape-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-15799" src="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Canape-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png" alt="Canape Theme Restaurant Menus" width="640" height="372" srcset="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Canape-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png 640w, https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Canape-Theme-Restaurant-Menus-768x446.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Canap√©‚Äôs default restaurant menu style ticks all the right boxes and looks great on mobile.</p></div>
<p>The theme‚Äôs simple but <a href="https://canapedemo.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">classic styling</a>¬†looks superb on smaller devices, integrates smoothly with <a href="https://en-ca.wordpress.org/plugins/open-table-widget/" target="_blank">OpenTable</a>, and enables you to showcase testimonials and featured menu items on your home page with ease.</p>
<p>Creating stylish menus with <a href="https://canapedemo.wordpress.com/menu/" target="_blank">multiple sections</a>¬†is a piece of cake, and you can easily rearrange their order on the WordPress backend. The one downside is that images aren‚Äôt easily integrated with menu items by default.</p>
<h4>Auberge from WebMan Design</h4>
<p>If you‚Äôre looking for a bit more control over menu options in particular, the free <a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/auberge/" target="_blank">Auberge restaurant theme</a>¬†for WordPress has a lot to offer. Auberge <a href="https://themedemos.webmandesign.eu/auberge/" target="_blank">looks great</a>¬†on all devices, has solid <a href="https://www.webmandesign.eu/manual/auberge/#" target="_blank">online documentation</a>, and enables you to build stylish <a href="https://themedemos.webmandesign.eu/auberge/menu/" target="_blank">multilevel menus</a>¬†with ease.</p>
<div id="attachment_15798" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Auberge-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png"><img class="wp-image-15798 size-full" src="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Auberge-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png" alt="Auberge Theme Restaurant Menus" width="640" height="425" srcset="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Auberge-Theme-Restaurant-Menus.png 640w, https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Auberge-Theme-Restaurant-Menus-768x510.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Auberge enables you to stylishly showcase individual dishes.</p></div>
<p>Auberge also plays nicely with the popular <a href="https://www.wpbeaverbuilder.com/" target="_blank">Beaver Builder</a>¬†page builder plugin, and can be used to create slick recipe sections via the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/webman-amplifier/" target="_blank">WebMan Amplifier plugin</a>.</p>
<h2>Standalone plugin solutions for restaurant menus</h2>
<p>On the other hand, if you‚Äôre looking to integrate menus with an existing theme, there are a number of <a href="https://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/resources/bon-apetit-six-of-the-best-wordpress-restaurant-menu-plugins" target="_blank">dedicated plugins</a>¬†you can use to get the job done quickly and easily. The following two stand out for their range of features and ease of use.</p>
<h4>Food and Drink Menu plugin</h4>
<div id="attachment_15801" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WordPress-Food-and-Drink-Menu-Plugin.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-15801" src="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WordPress-Food-and-Drink-Menu-Plugin.png" alt="WordPress Food and Drink Menu Plugin" width="640" height="202" srcset="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WordPress-Food-and-Drink-Menu-Plugin.png 640w, https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/WordPress-Food-and-Drink-Menu-Plugin-768x242.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The Food and Drink Menu plugin is highly rated, free, and gets the job done with no fuss.</p></div>
<p>The <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/food-and-drink-menu/" target="_blank">Food and Drink Menu</a>¬†plugin is designed to do exactly what its name suggests, enabling you to slot solid menu functionality into the restaurant site of your choosing. With rock solid ratings, <a href="https://themeofthecrop.com/2014/07/31/achieve-complex-menu-layouts-food-drink-menu" target="_blank">handy tutorials</a>, and a <a href="http://doc.themeofthecrop.com/plugins/food-and-drink-menu/user/" target="_blank">straightforward user guide</a>¬†to show you the way, this is a plugin you can start using with confidence on client sites in no time at all.</p>
<h4>FoodPress plugin</h4>
<div id="attachment_15800" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/FoodPress-WordPress-Plugin.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-15800" src="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/FoodPress-WordPress-Plugin.png" alt="FoodPress WordPress Plugin" width="640" height="179" srcset="https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/FoodPress-WordPress-Plugin.png 640w, https://www.godaddy.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/FoodPress-WordPress-Plugin-768x214.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">FoodPress covers you completely for menu options, and much more besides.</p></div>
<p>If you‚Äôre prepared to invest a little upfront cash to get the job done, <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/foodpress-restaurant-menu-reservation-plugin/6480595" target="_blank">FoodPress</a>¬†will have you covered for a very reasonable fee. In addition to built-in reservation and notification options, it comes with a genuinely impressive range of <a href="http://demo.myfoodpress.com/" target="_blank">menu formats</a>¬†to showcase your wares. The plugin also provides additional menu functionality in the form of location-specific menus, menu categorization options, and support for custom menu icons.</p>
<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>Savvy restaurant owners know that online menu presentation simply has to be on point, otherwise people will be taking their business elsewhere. Fortunately, there‚Äôs a range of easy-to-integrate WordPress solutions just sitting there waiting to be used.</p>
<p>Let‚Äôs recap the two basic options you have, along with our specific recommendations:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Go with a dedicated restaurant theme.</strong> <a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/canape/" target="_blank">Canap√©</a>¬†is a great choice if you‚Äôre looking for a simple yet elegant menu solution. However, <a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/auberge/" target="_blank">Auberge</a>¬†gives you a bit more power to play with across the board.</li>
<li><strong>Use a standalone menu plugin.</strong> The <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/food-and-drink-menu/" target="_blank">Food and Drink Menu</a>¬†plugin will get the job done quickly. If you want wider design and additional options, consider <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/foodpress-restaurant-menu-reservation-plugin/6480595" target="_blank">investing in FoodPress</a>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Got any tips for making your restaurant menu look good enough to eat? Get in touch via the comments section below and let us know!</p>
